<a class='reflink' href='../3.dcf/3.3.bpi.html#propositionbasicisomorphisms'>3.3.6</a>

<!-- 3.3.6 -->
<div class='toload proposition'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Proposition 3.3.6</span>
	Let $\mathcal{A}(X)\subseteq (H_X)^X$ and $\mathcal{A}(Y)\subseteq (H_Y)^Y$, and consider maps $\phi:Y\to X$ and $T:\mathcal{A}(X)\to\mathcal{A}(Y)$. Then
	<ol class='alphpar'>
		<li>
			$T$ is $\phi$-basic if and only if for all $y\in Y$,
			<div class='equation'>\[
				f(\phi(y))=g(\phi(y))\Longrightarrow Tf(y)=Tg(y),\qquad\forall f,g\in\mathcal{A}(X).\tag{3.3.3}
			\]</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
	In this case,
	<style>
	.alphparat2 {counter-reset: alphpar 1;}
	</style>
	<ol class='alphpar'><span class='alphparat2'></span>
		<li>
			the $(\phi,T)$-transform $\chi$ is unique.
		</li>
		
		<li>
			A section $\chi(y,\cdot)$ is injective if and only if
			<div class='equation'>\[
				Tf(y)=Tg(y)\Longrightarrow f(\phi(y))=g(\phi(y)),\qquad\forall f,g\in\mathcal{A}(X).\tag{3.3.4}
			\]</div>
		</li>
		
		<li>
			A section $\chi(y,\cdot)$ is surjective if and only if
			<div class='equation'>\[
				H_Y=\left\{Tf(y):f\in\mathcal{A}(X)\right\}.
			\]</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
	</p>
</div>